11#ifndef MODULES_VIDEO_CODING_PACKET_BUFFER_H_
12#define MODULES_VIDEO_CODING_PACKET_BUFFER_H_
13
14#include <memory>
15#include <queue>
16#include <set>
17#include <vector>
18
19#include "absl/base/attributes.h"
20#include "api/rtp_packet_info.h"
21#include "api/units/timestamp.h"
22#include "api/video/encoded_image.h"
23#include "modules/rtp_rtcp/source/rtp_packet_received.h"
24#include "modules/rtp_rtcp/source/rtp_video_header.h"
25#include "rtc_base/copy_on_write_buffer.h"
26#include "rtc_base/numerics/sequence_number_util.h"
27#include "rtc_base/thread_annotations.h"
28
29namespace webrtc {
30namespace video_coding {
31
32class PacketBuffer {
33 public:
34 struct Packet {
35 Packet() = default;
36 Packet(const RtpPacketReceived& rtp_packet,
37 const RTPVideoHeader& video_header);
38 Packet(const Packet&) = delete;
39 Packet(Packet&&) = delete;
40 Packet& operator=(const Packet&) = delete;
41 Packet& operator=(Packet&&) = delete;
42 ~Packet() = default;
43
44 VideoCodecType codec() const { return video_header.codec; }
45 int width() const { return video_header.width; }
46 int height() const { return video_header.height; }
47
48 bool is_first_packet_in_frame() const {
49 return video_header.is_first_packet_in_frame;
50 }
51 bool is_last_packet_in_frame() const {
52 return video_header.is_last_packet_in_frame;
53 }
54
55 // If all its previous packets have been inserted into the packet buffer.
56 // Set and used internally by the PacketBuffer.
57 bool continuous = false;
58 bool marker_bit = false;
59 uint8_t payload_type = 0;
60 uint16_t seq_num = 0;
61 uint32_t timestamp = 0;
62 int times_nacked = -1;
63
64 rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer video_payload;
65 RTPVideoHeader video_header;
66 };
67 struct InsertResult {
68 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<Packet>> packets;
69 // Indicates if the packet buffer was cleared, which means that a key
70 // frame request should be sent.
71 bool buffer_cleared = false;
72 };
73
74 // Both |start_buffer_size| and |max_buffer_size| must be a power of 2.
75 PacketBuffer(size_t start_buffer_size, size_t max_buffer_size);
76 ~PacketBuffer();
77
78 ABSL_MUST_USE_RESULT InsertResult
79 InsertPacket(std::unique_ptr<Packet> packet);
80 ABSL_MUST_USE_RESULT InsertResult InsertPadding(uint16_t seq_num);
81 void ClearTo(uint16_t seq_num);
82 void Clear();
83
84 void ForceSpsPpsIdrIsH264Keyframe();
85
86 private:
87 void ClearInternal();
88
89 // Tries to expand the buffer.
90 bool ExpandBufferSize();
91
92 // Test if all previous packets has arrived for the given sequence number.
93 bool PotentialNewFrame(uint16_t seq_num) const;
94
95 // Test if all packets of a frame has arrived, and if so, returns packets to
96 // create frames.
97 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<Packet>> FindFrames(uint16_t seq_num);
98
99 void UpdateMissingPackets(uint16_t seq_num);
100
101 // buffer_.size() and max_size_ must always be a power of two.
102 const size_t max_size_;
103
104 // The fist sequence number currently in the buffer.
105 uint16_t first_seq_num_;
106
107 // If the packet buffer has received its first packet.
108 bool first_packet_received_;
109
110 // If the buffer is cleared to |first_seq_num_|.
111 bool is_cleared_to_first_seq_num_;
112
113 // Buffer that holds the the inserted packets and information needed to
114 // determine continuity between them.
115 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<Packet>> buffer_;
116
117 absl::optional<uint16_t> newest_inserted_seq_num_;
118 std::set<uint16_t, DescendingSeqNumComp<uint16_t>> missing_packets_;
119
120 // Indicates if we should require SPS, PPS, and IDR for a particular
121 // RTP timestamp to treat the corresponding frame as a keyframe.
122 bool sps_pps_idr_is_h264_keyframe_;
123};
124
125} // namespace video_coding
126} // namespace webrtc
127
128#endif // MODULES_VIDEO_CODING_PACKET_BUFFER_H_
